<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/598: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-06T23:00:00+03:00">August 6,
                                    1940—11 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 7—9:01 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>979. Embassy’s telegram No. 978, August 6, 10 p.m. An understanding was
                            reached with Mikoyan to the effect that the English and Russian texts
                            shall be considered equally authentic. I left with him a note on the
                            subject reading as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Mr. People’s Commissar, it is my understanding, which I shall be
                                    glad to have you confirm to me that the English and Russian
                                    texts <pb facs="0470" n="458" xml:id="pg_458"/> of the exchange
                                    of notes we have just effected extending the commercial
                                    agreement shall be considered equally authentic.</p>
                                <p>Accept Mr. People’s Commissar the renewed assurances of my
                                    highest consideration.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Mikoyan stated that he will address a note to me tomorrow confirming my
                            understanding in this matter.<note n="73" xml:id="d322fn73">The Chargé
                                reported the receipt of this confirmation on August 7.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>